{
  "texts": [
    "AT-PR exhibits similar GE to PGD.",
    "AT-PR, though designed as a PR-targeted method, is ATinspired: it selects AEs from a set of PGD-generated candidates corresponding to different local optima.",
    "Consequently, as shown in Table 3 & 9, its GE aligns closely with that of PGD.",
    "A detailed theoretical analysis with its corresponding algorithm is provided in Appendix E.4.",
    "Optimization budget explains the GE gap between ALP and CLP: CLP shows higher GE than ALP, as ALP uses AEs in its optimization objective while CLP relies on clean inputs."
  ]
}